<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-60-1059 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper reports on the status of public opinion on nuclear energy inthe United States and worldwide. Recent polling results, including theCambridge Reports' May 1988 national poll, show that Americans view nuclearenergy as important and increasingly needed. Also the majority expectthat new nuclear plants probably will have to be built in the USA inthe years ahead. The National Science Board's Science and EngineeringIndicators-1987 reports that 56% of Americans think that nuclear energywill be the primary source of electricity 25 years from now. These viewsare shared also by other people in other countries i.e. Germany, France,Japan and Canada, which have a major investment in nuclear energy asa source of electricity. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>